{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018HQv5BhBCcWwnE6mH33T82","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the KARMA precondition logic:\n\n- probe **passes** → state already present → apply is SKIPPED\n- probe **fails** + `on_probe_fail=\"skip\"` → \"not yet present\" → run apply\n- probe **fails** + `on_probe_fail=\"error\"` → error, probe is retried\n\nSo for `mongo_env_ready`:\n- Probe: `kubectl -n mongodb get statefulset mongodb-replica >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n mongodb get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -q Running`\n- If this passes (StatefulSet exists or pods running) → apply is skipped, avoiding a destructive namespace rebuild\n- If this fails (no StatefulSet and no pods) → apply runs to create a fresh namespace with fault injection\n\nLooking back at the precondition.log, `mongo_env_ready` shows the probe passed with no apply following it, which means the cluster was already running and the fault injection setup was skipped. Meanwhile, `mongo_seed_fixture` had its probe fail (not enough docs in app.test), so the apply ran to seed the fixture.\n\nSo the fault injection was never actually applied—the precondition found an existing cluster from stage_01 and skipped the destructive apply. Now I need to check what the oracle is actually validating. Let me look at the oracle script to understand what's being tested, and then examine the current replica set state more carefully—all three members are healthy and synced, with three documents seeded, but there's something odd about the primary's sync status that I need to investigate. 's something else going on that I need to check against the oracle to understand what the actual failure condition is.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2538,"cache_read_input_tokens":44383,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2538},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2e442b48-7d78-4fe2-ab6c-6beac0660192","uuid":"01c277e6-388c-4c39-87c2-fbabcbcef1a8","request_id":"req_011CcfvkJNkEKmVr7QTBTGLd"}
